{
  "texts": [
    "What techniques underpin the evolution of LLMs' moral competence, and how do they foster its growth?",
    "We explore and explain the moral growth of LLMs based on experimental results, through their training techniques and Dewey's moral philosophy.",
    "Ethicists have long explored what humans ought to do but have often neglected how humans actually learn morality.",
    "Concerning this, Dewey employs a certain practical ethics to illustrate the process of moral learning, and more importantly, it also has the potential to serve as a theoretical foundation for improving the moral competence of machines.",
    "Dewey(2008a) argues from an ontological and organic perspective that morality can grow."
  ]
}